WEBVTT

00:01.410 --> 00:02.786
- YOU STILL WANNA HAVE MY BABY,
YOU CAN HAVE IT.

00:02.930 --> 00:03.715
- PEOPLE PAY A LOT OF MONEY
FOR A BABY TH ESE DAYS.

00:03.860 --> 00:05.589
- I CAN'T GIVE YOU MONEY
FOR THE BABY, ZOE.

00:05.720 --> 00:06.994
- I NEED HELP.

00:07.140 --> 00:08.892
- I KNOW THAT
YOU'RE WORKING VERY HARD,

00:09.040 --> 00:11.031
BUT YOU'RE GOING TO HAVE
TO FIGURE SOMETHING ELSE OUT.

00:11.180 --> 00:12.454
- SHE KISSED ME,
I TOLD YOU ABOUT IT.

00:12.590 --> 00:14.729
YOU ASKED ME TO FIRE HER,
I TRIED TO FIRE HER,

00:14.870 --> 00:16.007
I COULDN'T GO THROUGH WITH IT,

00:16.150 --> 00:17.549
I FELT LIKE HER FEELINGS
WERE HURT.

00:17.700 --> 00:19.281
HEY, CAN WE TALK?
- I DECIDED TO GO BACK TO WORK.

00:19.430 --> 00:20.943
- I UNDERSTAND
WHERE YOU'RE COMING FROM,

00:21.090 --> 00:22.216
BUT I'M NOT GOING ANYWHERE.

00:22.360 --> 00:23.975
I REALLY LIKE JASMINE
AND JABBAR.

00:24.120 --> 00:26.748
THIS IS FOR REAL.
- I THINK YOU SHOULD GO.

00:32.720 --> 00:34.950
[sighs]

00:35.100 --> 00:35.885
[Cults' Rave Onplays]

00:46.800 --> 00:50.759
- ON A BOAT,
ON MY SAILING SHIP

00:50.910 --> 00:54.380
ON MY OWN,
FAR AWAY FROM IT

00:54.530 --> 00:55.394
- OH.

00:55.530 --> 00:56.872
[groans]

00:57.020 --> 00:59.181
- BUT DON'T GIVE ME THIS

00:59.330 --> 01:03.266
I'LL PASS
IF THAT'S OKAY

01:03.400 --> 01:06.267
- MM, CROSBY, CROSBY, CROSBY,
GET UP, GET UP.

01:06.410 --> 01:08.366
COME ON.
YOU GOTTA GO.

01:08.510 --> 01:09.716
- WHAT IS IT?
- YOU GOTTA GO NOW.

01:09.860 --> 01:11.373
GET UP NOW!
- WHAT'S HAPPENING?

01:11.510 --> 01:12.784
- YOU GOTTA GO.
- OH, BOY, THIS HAPPENED.

01:12.930 --> 01:14.682
- MY MOTHER IS DROPPING JABBAR
OFF AT 7:30.

01:14.830 --> 01:17.060
THAT MEANS YOU GOT SEVEN MINUTES
TO GET UP AND GET OUT OF BED.

01:17.210 --> 01:18.552
COME ON.

01:18.690 --> 01:20.032
SHE'S NEVER BEEN LATE
FOR ANYTHING IN HER LIFE.

01:20.180 --> 01:21.727
- YOU WAN NA TALK ABOUT--
- OBVIOUSLY WE'LL TALK ABOUT IT.

01:21.870 --> 01:22.859
WE CAN'T TALK ABOUT IT
RIGHT NOW.

01:23.010 --> 01:23.999
WE GOT NO TIME.
GET UP.

01:24.150 --> 01:24.900
- OKAY, OKAY, I'M GOING.
I'M GOING.

01:25.050 --> 01:26.312
- [sighs]
OH, MAN.

01:26.460 --> 01:27.904
- DO YOU--ARE YOU--
IS EVERYTHING OKAY?

01:28.050 --> 01:28.948
- NO, EVERYTHING
IS NOT OKAY!

01:29.080 --> 01:30.809
- OKAY, I'M COMING.
HOLD ON.

01:30.950 --> 01:31.939
OH, BOY.

01:32.090 --> 01:33.227
- COME ON!
- OKAY, OKAY.

01:33.360 --> 01:34.679
I'M COMING.
I'M COMING, COMING, COMING.

01:34.810 --> 01:38.814
ALL RIGHT, UM--
- HERE, HERE, HERE.

01:38.960 --> 01:40.188
- GO, GO, GO,
GO, GO, GO, GO, GO.

01:40.340 --> 01:43.093
- UM...OKAY,
JASMINE, UH--

01:43.240 --> 01:44.719
- YEAH, I KNOW, I KNOW,
WE'LL TALK.

01:44.860 --> 01:46.304
WE'LL TALK LATER.

01:46.450 --> 01:49.897
- RAVE ON

01:50.040 --> 01:54.898
RAVE ON

02:00.360 --> 02:01.907
- HEY.
- HMM.

02:02.050 --> 02:04.018
- I WAS JUST COMING OVER HERE
TO SEE IF YOU NEEDED ANYTHING,

02:04.150 --> 02:05.492
BUT YOU'RE ALL SET.

02:05.640 --> 02:06.777
SO PEET'S.
- YUP.

02:06.910 --> 02:08.013
- THEY'RE GOOD.

02:08.160 --> 02:09.559
- I THOUGHT
IT MIGHT BE EASIER

02:09.710 --> 02:12.634
IF WE GAVE EACH OTHER
SOME SPACE FOR A LITTLE WHILE.

02:12.780 --> 02:16.022
- YEAH,
I...I GET THAT.

02:16.170 --> 02:17.740
- GREAT.

02:17.890 --> 02:20.950
- I MEAN, I TOTALLY UNDERSTAND
IF--IF YOU AND JOEL

02:21.100 --> 02:22.544
NEED TIME TO THINK ABOUT IT.

02:22.690 --> 02:25.579
I GET IT, SO I UNDERSTAND.
NO PROBLEM.

02:25.730 --> 02:27.448
- ZOE...

02:27.590 --> 02:30.718
THERE'S NOTHING FOR US
TO THINK ABOUT.

02:30.870 --> 02:34.556
WHAT YOU'RE ASKING
IS NOT GOING TO HAPPEN.

02:34.700 --> 02:37.077
WE DON'T NEED TIME
TO THINK ABOUT IT,

02:37.220 --> 02:40.701
WE NEED TIME TO GET OVER IT.

02:40.850 --> 02:43.045
WOULD YOU JUST SHUT
THE DOOR BEHIND YOU?

02:43.190 --> 02:46.057
- OH.

02:46.200 --> 02:48.748
OKAY.
- OKAY.

03:09.670 --> 03:12.457
- SO WHAT'S GOING ON WITH
JASMINE AND DR. PRESTIDGE?

03:12.600 --> 03:13.828
- WE'LL--WE'LL GET TO THAT,

03:13.980 --> 03:16.289
BUT WHAT'S WITH
THE FROSTINESS GOING ON

03:16.430 --> 03:18.534
WITH YOU AND THE OLD LADY?

03:18.680 --> 03:19.874
UH-OH.
- HEY.

03:20.020 --> 03:21.430
- HI.
- HEY, LADIES.

03:21.580 --> 03:23.571
- WHO'S MORE APPEALING
THAN THIS?

03:23.720 --> 03:25.335
NO ONE.
- NOBODY.

03:25.480 --> 03:26.435
- YOU'RE GIVING
THE WRONG MESSAGE.

03:26.580 --> 03:28.161
IT'S NOT A BIG DEAL AT ALL.

03:28.310 --> 03:31.029
I'M JUST--
[groans]

03:31.170 --> 03:33.138
- AMBER NEEDS A JOB.
SHE NEEDS SOME WORK.

03:33.280 --> 03:35.794
DO YOU GUYS HAVE ANYTHING
AT THE STUDIO THAT SHE COULD DO?

03:35.930 --> 03:37.898
- WOULD THAT HAVE BEEN NICE.
- SHE'S NEEDING SOME MONEY.

03:38.040 --> 03:39.314
- I LOVE MUSIC.
- SHE'S SO VERY MUSICAL.

03:39.460 --> 03:40.939
- CAN YOU BLAME ME?

03:41.080 --> 03:42.763
- YEAH, WE ALREADY HAVE
AN ASSISTANT.

03:42.910 --> 03:45.219
- I MEAN, WE WOULD LOVE
TO HAVE YOU BUT--

03:45.360 --> 03:47.760
- YOUR DAD WANTS
TO GIVE A SPEECH HERE.

03:47.910 --> 03:49.218
- OKAY.
BE RIGHT THERE, POP.

03:49.360 --> 03:51.112
- WHAT ARE
YOU TALKING ABOUT?

03:51.260 --> 03:54.468
- AMBER'S LOOKING FOR WORK,
BUT WE--YOU KNOW--

03:54.610 --> 03:55.816
- IF YOU HAD AN ASSISTANT?

03:55.950 --> 03:57.645
YEAH, YOU GUYS HAVE
A GREAT ASSISTANT.

03:57.780 --> 03:59.509
ACTUALLY, I'M WORKING
ON A CAMPAIGN.

03:59.650 --> 04:01.811
AND MAYBE
I CAN GET YOU ONBOARD.

04:01.960 --> 04:04.133
I DON'T KNOW IF
THERE'S ANY OPENINGS.

04:04.270 --> 04:06.238
BOBBY LITTLE--
HE'S RUNNING FOR CITY COUNCIL.

04:06.380 --> 04:07.404
- THIS GUY--HE USED
TO BE HER INTERN.

04:07.550 --> 04:08.653
WE CALLED HIM
"LI'I'I'LE BOBBY LITTLE."

04:08.800 --> 04:09.789
- YOU CALLED HIM
"LI'ITLE BOBBY LITTLE."

04:09.930 --> 04:11.511
- OH, WOW.
- I THINK YOU WOULD BE

04:11.660 --> 04:14.037
GREAT AT THAT.
- [whistles] COME HERE. COME.

04:14.180 --> 04:15.556
COME ON!
- WE'RE READY...

04:15.700 --> 04:18.043
- YEAH. I JUST WANT
TO SAY A FEW WORDS.

04:18.180 --> 04:19.875
NOTHING, NO BIG DEAL.
- I THINK THAT WOULD BE GREAT.

04:20.010 --> 04:21.739
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
'CAUSE I CAN'T HIRE HER,

04:21.880 --> 04:23.279
NOW YOU'RE GOING TO HIRE HER?
- NO, YOU HAVE AN ASSISTANT.

04:23.430 --> 04:25.807
IF YOU WOULD HAVE FIRED RACHEL,
YOU'D HAVE A SPOT OPEN.

04:25.950 --> 04:27.747
BUT YOU DIDN'T,
SO I'M GOING TO TRY.

04:27.880 --> 04:29.529
- ADAM?
- YEAH, SORRY.

04:29.680 --> 04:30.840
SORRY, POP.
- WHERE'S MOM?

04:30.990 --> 04:32.719
- YOU KNOW, AT MY AGE,
YOU START THINKING

04:32.850 --> 04:35.922
WELL, THERE JUST COULDN'T BE
ANY MORE SURPRISES,

04:36.060 --> 04:37.379
BUT, UH...
- DAD.

04:37.510 --> 04:39.193
- WELL, NO.
- THE BREAK IS ON--THIS IS IT.

04:39.340 --> 04:40.511
[screaming]

04:40.650 --> 04:44.063
- YEAH.
- QUIET, QUIET, QUIET, QUIET!

04:44.210 --> 04:45.416
- WHOO!
- SHH.

04:45.560 --> 04:47.516
- ARE YOU WORRIED
ABOUT A STORM?

04:47.660 --> 04:50.003
- NOPE.
LOOKS LIKE CLEAR SKIES AHEAD.

04:50.150 --> 04:51.071
- OH, MY GOD.

04:51.220 --> 04:54.735
[laughter]

04:54.880 --> 04:56.006
- [mouths]
A LOT OF LIFE LEFI' IN ME.

04:56.150 --> 05:02.111
[screaming]

05:02.260 --> 05:05.536
- WHOA!
- EEW!

05:05.680 --> 05:08.956
- HOLY--YOU'RE NOT AFRAID
OF NO STORM.

05:09.100 --> 05:12.718
[tapping keys]

05:16.210 --> 05:18.678
- I NEED YOU TO TAKE MAX
TO SCHOOL IN THE MORNING.

05:18.830 --> 05:20.684
I HAVE TO STOP
BY THE OFFICE.

05:20.830 --> 05:22.934
- OKAY.

05:23.080 --> 05:26.038
I THOUGHT YOU DIDN'T
START WORK UNTIL MONDAY.

05:26.180 --> 05:29.809
- I DON'T, BUT BOB
WANTS ME TO MEET THE TEAM, SO...

05:29.950 --> 05:33.420
- ALL RIGHT.

05:33.570 --> 05:36.038
HOW LONG ARE YOU
GOING TO BE MAD AT ME?

05:43.130 --> 05:44.358
- I DON'T KNOW.

05:44.510 --> 05:47.638
- HMM.

05:51.380 --> 05:52.108
[sighs]

05:53.800 --> 05:56.109
MAY GOD BLESS
AND KEEP YOU ALWAYS

05:56.250 --> 05:58.935
AND MAY YOUR WISHES
ALL COME TRUE

05:59.080 --> 06:01.219
MAY YOU ALWAYS DO
FOR OTHERS

06:01.360 --> 06:03.692
AND LET OTHERS DO FOR YOU

06:03.840 --> 06:06.217
MAY YOU BUILD A LADDER
TO THE STARS

06:06.360 --> 06:08.464
AND CLIMB ON EVERY RUNG

06:08.600 --> 06:10.909
AND MAY YOU STAY

06:11.060 --> 06:13.290
FOREVER YOUNG

06:13.440 --> 06:15.988
MAY YOU GROW UP
TO BE RIGHTEOUS

06:16.130 --> 06:18.098
MAY YOU GROW UP
TO BE TRUE

06:18.230 --> 06:20.812
MAY YOU ALWAYS KNOW
THE TRUTH

06:20.960 --> 06:22.951
AND SEE THE LIGHTS
SURROUNDING YOU

06:23.100 --> 06:25.785
MAY YOU ALWAYS BE
COURAGEOUS

06:25.930 --> 06:28.069
STAND UPRIGHT
AND BE STRONG

06:28.210 --> 06:30.030
AND MAY YOU STAY

06:30.180 --> 06:32.557
FOREVER YOUNG

06:32.700 --> 06:34.975
MAY YOU STAY

06:35.110 --> 06:38.113
FOREVER YOUNG

06:41.120 --> 06:44.988
- HEY, WE WOULD TOTALLY HIRE
AMBER IF WE HAD THE MONEY.

06:45.120 --> 06:46.530
I WOULD LOVE
TO HAVE HER WORKING HERE.

06:46.680 --> 06:48.193
I THINK IT'D BE REALLY FUN.

06:48.330 --> 06:49.672
- DON'T YOU THINK
IT'D BE SO GREAT

06:49.820 --> 06:51.264
WITH HER MUSIC AND EVERYTHING?
- NO, IT WOULD.

06:51.410 --> 06:54.743
BUT SHE NEEDS MONEY, AND WE'RE
NOT IN A POSITION TO PAY HER.

06:54.890 --> 06:55.640
- I DON'T KNOW HOW MUCH MONEY
SHE'S GOING TO MAKE

06:55.790 --> 06:58.896
ON A CAMPAIGN, BUT--

06:59.030 --> 07:00.065
- WELL, MAYBE IT WILL LEAD
TO SOMETHING.

07:00.210 --> 07:01.893
- YEAH.
-I THINK IT WAS COOL, THOUGH,

07:02.040 --> 07:04.759
OF KRISTINA TO OFFER, RIGHT?
- I THOUGHT IT WAS COOL TOO.

07:04.900 --> 07:08.597
- SO SPEAKING OF AMBER, UH,
TRYING TO GET A JOB,

07:08.730 --> 07:11.494
I SLEPT WITH JASMINE
THE OTHER DAY.

07:11.630 --> 07:14.190
- [coughs]

07:14.330 --> 07:15.945
- OOPS.

07:16.090 --> 07:18.467
I WAS HOPING THAT MAYBE YOU'VE
DONE THE SAME THING WITH SETH

07:18.610 --> 07:22.398
AND COULD ADVISE ME
ON SAID SITUATION.

07:22.540 --> 07:23.325
HAS THAT EVER HAPPENED?

07:23.470 --> 07:24.505
- MM.

07:24.650 --> 07:26.094
- THAT'S A YES?

07:26.230 --> 07:27.982
[chuckles] GOOD, SO THIS IS
SOMETHING THAT HAPPENS.

07:28.130 --> 07:29.472
PE-PEOPLE DO THIS.

07:29.620 --> 07:32.544
- IT'S THE MOTHER OF YOUR CHILD,
YOU KNOW.

07:32.690 --> 07:34.442
IT'S A PRETTY SPECIAL
CONNECTION.

07:34.590 --> 07:35.682
- YEAH...

07:35.830 --> 07:37.513
YEAH, IT'S COMPLICATED.

07:37.660 --> 07:40.345
YOU KNOW, WE WERE TELLING JABBAR
THAT WE WEREN'T GETTING MARRIED,

07:40.490 --> 07:43.141
AND IT WAS KIND OF SAD.

07:43.290 --> 07:44.518
WE WERE--WE WERE BOTH SAD.

07:44.670 --> 07:47.116
AND THEN WE STARTED
DRINKING WINE, AND--

07:47.250 --> 07:48.569
AND THEN...
[laughs]

07:48.700 --> 07:50.144
YOU KNOW.
- I KNOW.

07:50.290 --> 07:51.734
- I HAVEN'T TALKED TO HER.

07:51.880 --> 07:53.324
I DON'T REALLY KNOW WHAT
I'M SUPPOSED TO SAY TO HER.

07:53.470 --> 07:55.392
DO YOU THINK THIS IS GOING
TO MAKE EVERYTHING DIFFERENT?

07:55.540 --> 07:58.646
- IT DEPENDS ON WHETHER OR NOT

07:58.780 --> 08:02.955
YOU WANT EVERYTHING
TO BE DIFFERENT.

08:03.100 --> 08:06.820
- MM-HMM.

08:06.960 --> 08:08.689
WHAT IF I DON'T KNOW?

08:16.150 --> 08:19.597
- SO YOU DID THE EMBARCADERO
YESTERDAY?

08:19.740 --> 08:20.809
AND YOU WERE ON TODAY?

08:20.940 --> 08:21.929
CAN YOU CALL
REPRESENTATIVE PORTER

08:22.080 --> 08:24.492
TO MAKE SURE
THAT HE'S ON BOARD?

08:24.640 --> 08:25.971
TERRIFIC. ALL RIGHT, GREAT.
AH...

08:26.120 --> 08:27.496
KRISTI NA!

08:27.640 --> 08:29.915
- HI.

08:30.060 --> 08:31.573
HEY.
- THANK GOD YOU'RE HERE.

08:31.710 --> 08:32.745
- HOW ARE YOU?

08:32.890 --> 08:34.118
- READY TO HIT THE GROUND
RUNNING?

08:34.270 --> 08:35.532
- SO NICE TO SEE YOU.
WOW, YOU LOOK GREAT.

08:35.680 --> 08:36.715
- THANK YOU, THANK YOU,
THANK YOU.

08:36.860 --> 08:38.259
- GROWN UP.

08:38.410 --> 08:39.752
- DONNA, CAN YOU SEND
KRISTINA MY CALENDAR,

08:39.890 --> 08:41.027
GET HER SET UP WITH EVERYTHING
THAT SHE NEEDS,

08:41.170 --> 08:43.343
AND GET HER DIRECTIONS TO
THE S.E.I.U. MEETING TOMORROW?

08:43.480 --> 08:44.378
- ANYTHING YOU NEED.
- OH.

08:44.520 --> 08:45.919
- I'M KRISTINA.
- HI, DONNA.

08:46.070 --> 08:47.139
THE MEETING'S HERE,
AND THE NOTES FOR THE MEETING

08:47.280 --> 08:48.622
ARE ON YOUR DESK.

08:48.760 --> 08:50.079
- WELL, YOU PROBABLY DON'T NEED
DIRECTIONS FOR THE MEETING.

08:50.210 --> 08:51.552
- THERE'S A MEETING HERE
TOMORROW?

08:51.700 --> 08:53.144
- YES, OH, CRAP.
DID YOU NOT GET A CALL?

08:53.290 --> 08:55.144
- I DIDN'T GET A CALL.
- I'M SORRY, IS THIS A PROBLEM?

08:55.290 --> 08:58.009
- I'M ACTUALLY TAKING MY SON
TO THE DINOSAUR EXHIBIT.

08:58.150 --> 08:59.902
TOMORROW'S SATURDAY,
SO I THOUGHT I WOULD BE OFF.

09:00.050 --> 09:01.256
- I AM SO SORRY.
- THAT'S OKAY.

09:01.400 --> 09:03.118
- DONNA, WILL YOU PLEASE
GO YELL AT SOMEBODY?

09:03.260 --> 09:05.535
- YES, I'M SO SORRY, WE'RE STILL
TRYING TO WORK OUT THE KINKS.

09:05.680 --> 09:07.261
- HEADS ARE GOING
TO ROLL FOR THIS.

09:07.400 --> 09:08.674
- DON'T MAKE ANY HEADS ROLL.

09:08.820 --> 09:10.219
- I PROMISE YOU.
- IT'S FINE.

09:10.370 --> 09:11.928
- PLEASE TELL ME YOU CAN MAKE
THIS MEETING TOMORROW.

09:12.060 --> 09:14.119
I DON'T HAVE TO TELL YOU WHAT
AN ENDORSEMENT FROM THE S.E.I.U.

09:14.270 --> 09:15.919
WOULD MEAN TO US.
- I KNOW. I WILL BE HERE.

09:16.070 --> 09:18.277
- I NEED YOU ON THIS.
- I'M HERE, I'M HERE FOR YOU.

09:18.410 --> 09:19.513
OKAY?
- OKAY, GOOD.

09:19.660 --> 09:20.820
- COME ON.
- WE'RE GOING TO WIN THIS.

09:20.970 --> 09:22.414
- COME ON, DONNA.
- YEAH.

09:22.560 --> 09:24.073
- DONNA, GET HER THE INFO.
KRISTINA, LET'S GO.

09:24.210 --> 09:25.450
- YES.
- COME ON, LET'S GO UP HERE.

09:25.590 --> 09:28.479
- TH ERE'S--OKAY.
WINNER, I'M--I'M COMING.

09:28.630 --> 09:30.188
[knocking on door]

09:30.320 --> 09:32.663
- HI.
- HEY.

09:32.810 --> 09:34.732
- I THINK I NEED TO QUIT.
- WHY IS THAT?

09:34.880 --> 09:36.734
HAVE YOU BRO||(\IEC|)\I SOMETHING?

09:36.880 --> 09:38.290
I REALLY HOPED THAT EVERYTHING
WOULD BLOW OVER,

09:38.430 --> 09:39.499
BUT IT'S NOT.
AT ALL.

09:39.640 --> 09:41.221
I FEEL LIKE
I JUST RUINED EVERYTHING

09:41.370 --> 09:44.407
OVER ONE DRUNK MISTAKE.

09:44.540 --> 09:47.543
- SO YOU WANT TO THROW IT
ALL AWAY OVER ONE DRUNK MISTAKE.

09:47.690 --> 09:49.305
- YEAH.

09:49.450 --> 09:51.338
I DON'T KNOW WHAT
OTHER CHOICE I HAVE.

09:51.480 --> 09:53.892
- I THINK LIFE MIGHT GO ON.
YOU'RE NOT QUITTING.

09:54.040 --> 09:55.826
- REALLY?
- YES, REALLY.

09:55.970 --> 09:57.130
IT'S GOING TO BLOW OVER.

09:57.280 --> 09:58.440
YOU JUST HAVE TO GIVE IT
A LITTLE TIME.

09:58.590 --> 10:01.070
BETWEEN, YOU AND ME,
IT'S NOT EVEN ABOUT ADAM.

10:01.220 --> 10:03.620
IT'S STUFF HE'S DEALING
WITH AT HOME WITH HIS WIFE.

10:03.770 --> 10:06.079
- HIS WIFE KNOWS?
- YES, HIS WIFE KNOWS.

10:06.220 --> 10:07.494
- OH, MY GOD.

10:07.640 --> 10:08.868
- DESPITE MY ADVICE
NOT TO TELL HER.

10:09.020 --> 10:12.183
- SHE MUST HATE ME.
- YEAH, SHE PROBABLY DOES.

10:12.330 --> 10:13.911
BUT, HEY, SHE HATED ME
TWO MONTHS AGO.

10:14.060 --> 10:16.051
I MEAN, SHE REALLY
WANTED TO KILL ME.

10:16.200 --> 10:18.259
AND NOW
SHE SEEMS TO LIKE ME.

10:18.410 --> 10:19.786
- REALLY?
- YEAH.

10:19.920 --> 10:21.956
- HOW'D YOU GET HER
TO FORGIVE YOU?

10:22.100 --> 10:23.715
- I DELIVERED HER BABY.
- OH.

10:23.860 --> 10:25.373
- THAT MIGHT NOT
BE AN OPTION FOR YOU,

10:25.520 --> 10:29.752
SO YOU MIGHT HAVE TO THINK
OF SOMETHING DIFFERENT.

10:29.900 --> 10:34.416
- [sighs]
I FEEL SO STUPID.

10:34.560 --> 10:37.040
- HEY, IT'S OKAY.

10:37.180 --> 10:39.068
YOU DON'T NEED TO FEEL STUPID.

10:39.220 --> 10:41.871
YOU'RE A GOOD PERSON.
YOU SCREWED UP.

10:42.020 --> 10:43.874
YOU MADE A MISTAKE.
YOU'RE HUMAN.

10:44.020 --> 10:46.636
THAT'S WHAT WE DO.
- OKAY.

10:46.780 --> 10:49.465
THANK YOU.
- YOU'RE WELCOME.

10:49.610 --> 10:51.714
NOW GO WORK.
YEAH?

10:51.850 --> 10:54.603
- YEAH.
OKAY. [laughs]

10:54.750 --> 10:57.878
- CHOP CHOP?
- OKAY.

11:12.910 --> 11:15.526
- HEY.
- HI, KIDDO.

11:15.670 --> 11:17.877
- HOW'S IT GOING?
- GOOD.

11:18.020 --> 11:19.419
WORKING HARD?
- OH, YEAH.

