20:15.040 --> 20:16.928
[TV in background]

20:17.070 --> 20:18.822
- BEGIN BY ASKING
A YES-OR-NO QUESTION

20:18.970 --> 20:20.790
ABOUT THE OTHER PLAYER'S
CHARACTER.

20:20.940 --> 20:23.591
- MAX?
- ...CHARACTER'S PERSONALITY...

20:25.460 --> 20:27.519
MAX!
WHERE ARE YOU?

20:39.440 --> 20:40.987
[coins jingle]

20:52.590 --> 20:54.103
- I'D HAVE TO ASK MY BROTHER,

20:54.250 --> 20:55.410
BUT I THINK IF YOU GUYS
ARE WILLING TO PAY THE RATE,

20:55.560 --> 20:56.788
HE COULD BE AGREEABLE
TO BEING AVAILABLE

20:56.940 --> 20:58.100
FOR 24 HOURS A DAY.
[knock at door]

20:58.250 --> 20:59.217
COME ON IN.

20:59.360 --> 21:00.839
- I'M SO SORRY
TO INTERRUPT.

21:00.980 --> 21:02.595
YOUR DAUGHTER'S ON THE PHONE.
SHE SAYS IT'S URGENT.

21:02.740 --> 21:06.153
- OKAY.
ONE SECOND, GUYS.

21:06.290 --> 21:07.564
HADDIE, YOU OKAY?

21:07.710 --> 21:10.702
[tires screeching]

21:10.850 --> 21:12.647
I CANNOT BELIEVE THIS, HADDIE!
HOW COULD YOU LET THIS HAPPEN?

21:12.780 --> 21:14.577
- I SAID I'M SORRY.
CAN YOU PLEASE NOT YELL?

21:14.720 --> 21:16.438
I'M SCARED.
I'M SORRY.

21:16.580 --> 21:17.956
- I'M NOT--I'M NOT YELLING.

21:18.100 --> 21:18.759
OKAY, LISTEN, YOU JUST GOT
TO STAY AT THE HOUSE

21:18.890 --> 21:20.642
AND MAKE SURE THAT YOU'RE THERE

21:20.790 --> 21:22.473
IN CASE MAX COMES HOME
OR CALLS

21:22.620 --> 21:24.440
OR ANYBODY CALLS, OKAY?
- OKAY.

21:24.590 --> 21:25.921
- I'M GONNA GO TO THE MUSEUM.

21:26.070 --> 21:27.059
- OKAY, THE POLICE ARE HERE.
- HADDIE, WAIT.

21:27.210 --> 21:28.552
YOU GOT TO LET 'EM KNOW
THAT HE'S AUTISTIC

21:28.700 --> 21:29.792
AND THAT HE'S GONNA BEHAVE
ERRATICALLY

21:29.940 --> 21:31.384
AND THAT HE'S NOT USED
TO BEING ALONE.

21:31.530 --> 21:32.485
YOU GOT THAT?
- I KNOW.

21:32.630 --> 21:33.597
- DO YOU HEAR ME?
- I KNOW.

21:33.740 --> 21:35.389
- HADDIE.
- OKAY. I WILL.

21:35.530 --> 21:36.315
I'LL TELL THEM.
both: OKAY.

21:36.460 --> 21:38.451
- BYE.
HI.

21:39.600 --> 21:41.773
[beep]
- CALL KRISTINA.

21:41.920 --> 21:43.774
- CALLING CROSBY.

21:43.920 --> 21:46.320
- CALL KRISTINA.

21:46.470 --> 21:48.677
- CALLING DRY CLEANER'S.

21:48.820 --> 21:51.402
- OH, MY GOD!
CALL KRISTINA.

21:51.550 --> 21:52.471
- YOU AND MOM
HAVE FUN LAST NIGHT?

21:52.620 --> 21:54.679
- UH-HUH.
WE WATCHED NEMO.

21:54.830 --> 21:57.378
- OOH.
NEMO,THAT'S A GOOD ONE.

21:57.520 --> 21:59.033
- BUT MOM DIDN'T SEE THE END.

21:59.170 --> 22:01.445
SHE HAD TO GO TO HER ROOM,
BECAUSE SHE GOT TOO SAD.

22:01.590 --> 22:03.410
- WELL, IT'S KIND
OF A SAD MOVIE.

22:03.560 --> 22:06.279
- I GUESS.

22:06.420 --> 22:07.899
I WASN'T SUPPOSED
TO TELL YOU

22:08.050 --> 22:11.076
THAT SHE WAS CRYING.

22:11.220 --> 22:12.562
CAN WE GET ICE CREAM?

22:14.120 --> 22:15.701
- YEAH. ONLY IF YOU BEAT ME
THERE FIRST.

22:15.850 --> 22:18.296
- OH, YES.
OH! OW!

22:18.440 --> 22:19.361
- OH, BUDDY.
ARE YOU OKAY?

22:19.510 --> 22:20.465
- OW!
- WHAT HAPPENED?

22:20.610 --> 22:22.430
YOUR WRIST?

22:22.580 --> 22:24.332
HOLD ON, HOLD ON.
JUST HOLD IT STILL.

22:24.480 --> 22:26.232
- IT HURTS.

22:26.370 --> 22:27.507
- HEY, YOU HEAR ANYTHING?

22:27.650 --> 22:28.685
- NO, NOTHING.

22:28.830 --> 22:30.377
SO YOU DIDN'T FIND HIM?

22:30.520 --> 22:31.748
- NO, I WENT THROUGH THE ENTIRE
MUSEUM LIKE FIVE TIMES.

22:31.900 --> 22:34.039
I TALKED TO EVERY
SECURITY GUARD. NOTHING.

22:34.180 --> 22:35.989
LISTEN, CAN YOU THINK
OF ANYTHING ELSE THAT HE SAID?

22:36.140 --> 22:37.721
IS THERE ANY OTHER PLACE
THAT HE MIGHT BE?

22:37.870 --> 22:40.179
CAN YOU THINUKMOF ANYTHING?

22:40.320 --> 22:41.969
NO.
I MEAN, I DON'T KNOW.

22:42.110 --> 22:43.111
I'M SORRY, DAD.

22:43.250 --> 22:44.387
- IT'S OKAY, ALL RIGHT?

22:44.530 --> 22:45.838
WE'RE GONNA FIND HIM.

22:45.980 --> 22:47.288
- I DIDN'T THINK
THAT HE WAS JUST GONNA LEAVE.

22:47.430 --> 22:48.738
- JUST STAY PUT, ALL RIGHT?

22:48.880 --> 22:50.984
I'LL BE HOME IN A LITTLE BIT.
I LOVE YOU.

22:58.160 --> 23:00.264
- THIS IS OFFICIALLY
THE LITTLEST BABY

23:00.410 --> 23:01.308
THAT I HAVE EVER HELD.

23:01.440 --> 23:02.543
- THIS IS?
- MM-HMM.

23:02.690 --> 23:04.476
- THIS ONE RIGHT HERE.

23:04.620 --> 23:06.656
- WOW.

23:06.790 --> 23:09.509
- [laughs]
I MEAN, NOT THAT I'VE HELD

23:09.660 --> 23:10.684
TOO MANY BABIES.

23:10.830 --> 23:12.798
NONE OF MY FRIENDS
HAVE THEM YET.

23:15.460 --> 23:18.520
- I HAD TWO BY YOUR AGE.

23:18.670 --> 23:21.252
- THAT'S TRUE.

23:21.400 --> 23:24.085
I AM FALLING BEHIND.

23:24.230 --> 23:25.390
SLACKIN'.

23:25.540 --> 23:26.461
I'M A LATE BLOOMER.

23:26.610 --> 23:28.259
- wiggles,
shrieks]

23:28.400 --> 23:30.322
- OHH.

23:30.470 --> 23:32.745
- [babbles]
- I KNOW.

23:32.890 --> 23:34.027
I KNOW.

23:34.170 --> 23:35.307
[muttering]

23:35.440 --> 23:38.750
DON'T--THAT'S MY NOSE.

23:38.900 --> 23:40.231
- SO HERE'S WHAT I'M THINKING--

23:40.380 --> 23:41.995
THE PARK, THE ONE
WITH THE BIG, HONKIN' SLIDE?

23:42.140 --> 23:45.655
- YEAH.
- THEN LIBRARY FOR STORY HOUR.

23:45.800 --> 23:48.177
- PARK AND STORY HOUR?
- YEAH.

23:48.320 --> 23:49.764
IT'S ON.
- YES!

23:49.910 --> 23:51.559
[knock at door]
COMING!

23:51.700 --> 23:54.498
WHO IS IT?

23:54.640 --> 23:56.449
- HEY.
- HI, ZOE.

23:56.600 --> 23:57.521
- WHAT'S UP, PRETTY GIRL?

23:57.670 --> 23:59.399
- GIVE ME JUST A MINUTE,
OKAY?

24:02.710 --> 24:04.439
- HI.
- I DON'T WANT HER TO SEE YOU.

24:04.580 --> 24:06.844
IT'S, YOU KNOW,
A LITTLE HARD TO EXPLAIN.

24:06.990 --> 24:10.858
- WELL, I JUST CAME TO TELL YOU
THAT TROY IS NOT A BAD GUY.

24:11.000 --> 24:12.956
- ZOE...

24:13.100 --> 24:14.089
- I HAVEN'T HAD

24:14.240 --> 24:16.856
WHAT YOU WOULD CALL
A CUSHY LIFE, OKAY?

24:17.000 --> 24:19.241
AND TROY JUST THINKS
THAT THIS COULD FINALLY MAKE

24:19.380 --> 24:20.586
THINGS EASIER FOR ME.

24:20.730 --> 24:22.937
I KNOW IT LOOKS
LIKE HE'S BEING A HUGE JERK,

24:23.080 --> 24:25.355
BUT IT'S JUST
'CAUSE HE REALLY LOVES ME.

24:25.490 --> 24:26.593
YOU KNOW?

24:26.740 --> 24:30.949
- ALL RIGHT.

24:31.090 --> 24:36.392
- YOU'VE BEEN
SO NICE TO ME.

24:36.540 --> 24:38.986
AND YOU'RE THIS AMAZING WOMAN

24:39.130 --> 24:40.438
THAT'S DONE
ALL THESE AMAZING THINGS,

24:40.580 --> 24:42.719
AND I'M JUST SOME PATHETIC GIRL

24:42.860 --> 24:43.849
THAT LISTENS
TO WHATEVER HER BOYFRIEND

24:43.990 --> 24:45.025
TELLS HER TO DO, RIGHT?

24:45.170 --> 24:46.125
- NO, ZOE.

24:46.270 --> 24:48.067
YOU'RE NOT PATHETIC.

24:48.210 --> 24:49.586
YOU'RE STRONG.

24:49.720 --> 24:52.348
YOU'RE PROBABLY STRONGER
THAN YOU KNOW.

24:52.490 --> 24:56.039
BUT RIGHT NOW I HAVE TO TAKE
MY DAUGHTER TO THE PARK.

24:59.530 --> 25:01.316
- I'M SO SORRY.

25:01.460 --> 25:04.634
- ME TOO.

25:04.770 --> 25:07.113
I WOULD HAVE BEEN A GREAT MOTHER
TO YOUR BABY.

25:09.400 --> 25:11.391
- NO, WE DON'T HAVE ANY IDEA
WHERE HE MIGHT BE RIGHT NOW,

25:11.540 --> 25:14.395
BUT, IF YOU HEAR ANYTHING,
JUST PLEASE GIVE ME A CALL BACK.

25:14.540 --> 25:15.404
ALL RIGHT.
THANK YOU.

25:15.540 --> 25:17.121
- I FOUND THIS PICTURE OF MAX

25:17.270 --> 25:18.714
IN THE SWEATSHIRT
HE WAS WEARING.

25:18.860 --> 25:21.237
WHO WERE YOU TALKING TO?
- GREAT.

25:21.380 --> 25:23.519
THE POLICE ASKED ME TO CALL
ALL OF MAX'S FRIENDS,

25:23.660 --> 25:25.616
AND SINCE HE DOESN'T HAVE ANY
FRIENDS,

25:25.760 --> 25:27.512
I'M JUST GOING DOWN THE LIST
OF HIS CLASS

25:27.660 --> 25:28.934
AND CALLING
ALL THOSE HOUSEHOLDS.

25:29.070 --> 25:31.630
AND NOW I'M GONNA TRY
YOUR MOTHER.

25:31.770 --> 25:34.489
AGAIN .

25:34.630 --> 25:36.666
- [overlapping comments]
- TO GO DO ALL THE DRINKING

25:36.810 --> 25:38.630
WITH THE COLLEGE STUDENTS.
- I KNEW YOU WERE

25:38.770 --> 25:40.112
GONNA SAY THAT.
I WAS GONNA SAY THAT TOO.

25:40.260 --> 25:42.046
[laughter]

25:44.810 --> 25:45.560
- AND IT GOES STRAIGHT
TO VOICE MAIL.

25:45.710 --> 25:47.154
I CAN'T BELIEVE THIS.

25:49.510 --> 25:51.569
[sighs]

26:29.170 --> 26:37.555
- WALK 1/2 BLOCK UP SHATTUCK
TO DOWNTOWN BERKELEY B.A.R.T.

26:37.690 --> 26:40.762
EXCUSE ME, SIR.
EXCUSE ME, SIR.

26:40.900 --> 26:42.595
MY NAME IS MAX BRAVERMAN,
AND I'M LOOKING

26:42.730 --> 26:43.765
FOR THE DOWNTOWN BERKELEY
B.A.R.T. STATION.

26:43.910 --> 26:45.662
- YOU GOT ANY MONEY?

26:48.570 --> 26:51.323
- HEY, HEY,
WATCH IT, MAN.

26:51.470 --> 26:56.601
[sirens wailing]

26:56.750 --> 27:00.334
[traffic and city noise]

27:08.660 --> 27:09.513
- HEY, LITTLE MAN.

27:09.660 --> 27:10.479
HOW YOU DOING?
HEY.

27:10.620 --> 27:11.894
- IT HURTS.

27:12.040 --> 27:13.962
- I KNOW, BUT WE'RE GONNA
GET YOU FIXED UP.

27:14.110 --> 27:16.977
SORRY ABOUT THE WAIT, MAN.

27:17.110 --> 27:18.281
I GOT HERE
AS FAST AS I COULD.

27:18.420 --> 27:19.899
I WAS COMING DOWN
FROM THE CAL GAME,

27:20.050 --> 27:21.802
AND TRAFFIC ON THE EMBARCADERO
WAS A NIGHTMARE.

27:21.950 --> 27:23.838
- DID WE WIN?

27:23.980 --> 27:27.290
- WE WERE UP 14-9
WHEN I LEFT.

27:27.430 --> 27:29.489
- YOU LEFT IN THE MIDDLE
OF A CAL GAME

27:29.640 --> 27:30.390
TO COME DOWN HERE?

27:30.540 --> 27:32.269
THAT'S...
[laughs]

27:32.400 --> 27:33.674
THAT WAS REALLY NICE.

27:33.820 --> 27:35.674
THANK YOU.

27:35.820 --> 27:37.503
- THIS SURE IS A BEAUTY.

27:37.650 --> 27:39.197
- DAD, IT HURTS.

27:39.340 --> 27:40.648
- I KNOW. HE'S GONNA FIX IT.
- TAKE MY HAND.

27:40.790 --> 27:42.405
THAT'S OKAY.

27:42.550 --> 27:44.757
NOW GIVE ME A SQUEEZE
EVERY TIME IT HURTS, OKAY?

27:44.900 --> 27:47.277
NOW, IF IT HURTS REALLY BAD,

27:47.420 --> 27:48.387
SQUEEEEZE REALLY HARD.

27:48.520 --> 27:50.932
ALL RIGHT?

27:51.080 --> 27:54.459
PSST, WHAT KIND OF ICE CREAM
DID YOU GET?

27:54.600 --> 27:56.454
- A SNOW CONE.
- NICE.

27:56.600 --> 27:57.635
- MY DAD DIDN'T LET ME EAT IT.

27:57.770 --> 27:59.180
HE MADE ME PUT IT ON MY WRIST.

27:59.330 --> 28:00.638
- THAT'S CAUSE YOUR DAD'S
A REALLY SMART GUY,

28:00.780 --> 28:02.941
BECAUSE HE DID
THE EXACT RIGHT THING.

28:03.090 --> 28:04.364
NOW I WANT YOU TO KEEP ICE
ON YOUR WRIST

28:04.510 --> 28:05.886
FOR THE NEXT 24 HOURS, OKAY?

28:06.020 --> 28:08.500
20 MINUTES ON, 20 MINUTES OFF.

28:08.650 --> 28:09.856
- SO IT'S NOT BROKEN?

28:09.990 --> 28:11.548
- IT'S JUST A MINOR SPRAIN.

28:11.690 --> 28:13.408
BUT I AM GONNA SEND YOU GUYS
HOME WITH SOME REAL ICE PACKS

28:13.550 --> 28:15.689
SO YOU CAN SAVE THE ICE CREAM
FOR YOUR TUMMY.

28:15.830 --> 28:16.899
- [giggIeSI

28:17.040 --> 28:18.655
- I KNOW
WHERE THE ICE PACKS ARE.

28:18.800 --> 28:20.449
CAN I GET THEM?
- YEAH, GO FOR IT.

28:29.150 --> 28:30.765
JASMINE AND JABBAR
HAVE SPENT, YOU KNOW,

28:30.910 --> 28:31.831
A FEW AFTERNOONS HERE, SO...

28:31.980 --> 28:33.254
HE LIKES TO HELP ME OUT.

28:33.400 --> 28:35.152
- YEAH.
HE'S A GOOD HELPER.

28:35.290 --> 28:38.157
- YEAH.

28:39.540 --> 28:41.599
I REALLY CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU LEFT IN THE MIDDLE

28:41.750 --> 28:43.194
OF A CAL GAME.

28:43.340 --> 28:44.671
I MEAN, THAT'S...

28:44.820 --> 28:46.811
YOU DO THAT
FOR ALL YOUR PATIENTS?

28:46.960 --> 28:49.542
- WELL, I WOULDN'T
ORDINARILY LEAVE A SEAT

28:49.690 --> 28:52.614
ON THE 50-YARD LINE
IN THE SECOND QUARTER.

28:52.760 --> 28:55.866
BUT HE'S WORTH IT.

28:58.390 --> 28:59.584
- YOU KNOW WHOSE JOB
WOULD BE PERFECT?

28:59.730 --> 29:01.618
- I CANNOT DO THAT.
I WILL GET IN TROUBLE.

29:01.770 --> 29:03.453
THAT IS NOT HAPPENING.

29:03.600 --> 29:04.521
FORGET IT.

29:04.670 --> 29:06.422
- KRISTINA, IT'S ADAM AGAIN.

29:06.570 --> 29:08.151
I AM STARTING
TO GET WORRIED ABOUT YOU TOO.

29:08.290 --> 29:09.359
COULD YOU PLEASE GIVE ME
A CALL BACK?

29:09.500 --> 29:11.912
THANK YOU.
BYE.

29:12.060 --> 29:14.631
- OKAY, HERE'S WHAT
WE HAVE SO FAR, MR. BRAVERMAN...

29:14.780 --> 29:16.224
[laughter]
- WE'RE ALL SET.

29:16.370 --> 29:17.951
- I'M WAY TOO OLD FOR THAT.

29:18.100 --> 29:19.886
- SHE'S ON IT, GUYS.
- BOBBY, I'M NOT DOING THAT.

29:20.030 --> 29:21.258
- YOU'RE ON IT.

29:21.410 --> 29:25.301
- DON'T LET HIM DO IT.
- NO.

29:29.520 --> 29:32.648
SORRY.

29:32.800 --> 29:34.688
- WE HAVE A SQUAD CAR
ON THE WAY, AND LIKE I SAID...

29:34.840 --> 29:35.659
[cell phone rings]
- EXCUSE ME.

29:35.800 --> 29:37.313
- HEY.
- ADAM.

29:37.460 --> 29:39.496
- HE'S ALL RIGHT.
METRO COP FOUND HIM IN OAKLAND

29:39.630 --> 29:41.359
WALKING AROUND, AND THEY'RE
GONNA BRING HIM HOME.

29:41.500 --> 29:42.467
- FOUND WHO?

29:42.600 --> 29:44.488
- MAX.

29:44.640 --> 29:46.801
LOOK, HONEY, I'LL EXPLAIN
EVERYTHING LATER, OKAY?

29:46.950 --> 29:49.327
JUST COME HOME.

29:51.130 --> 29:53.781
[police radio chatter]

29:55.720 --> 29:58.166
- YEAH, WELL, MY PHONE WAS OFF
FOR ONE MEETING.

29:58.310 --> 29:59.789
[siren wailing]
THAT'S IT.

29:59.930 --> 30:02.376
I MEAN, YOU COULD HAVE...
YOU COULD HAVE TEXTED ME OR--

30:02.520 --> 30:03.930
- LET'S JUST TRY AND STAY CALM
AND GIVE HIM SOME SPACE,

30:04.070 --> 30:05.583
ALL RIGHT?

30:05.730 --> 30:07.038
TRY NOT TO SMOTHER HIM.

30:07.180 --> 30:09.410
- I'M NOT GONNA SMOTHER HIM.

30:09.560 --> 30:10.970
I JUST WANT HIM HOME,

30:11.110 --> 30:12.975
AND I'M JUST GONNA MAKE SURE
HE'S OKAY.

30:13.120 --> 30:14.940
- HEY, LOOK WHO'S HOME.
- HI, HONEY.

30:15.080 --> 30:16.399
- I GOT TO RIDE IN A COP CAR.
- YEAH.

30:16.530 --> 30:17.770
- PRETTY FUN.

30:17.910 --> 30:19.150
- WELCOME HOME
TO THE ADVENTURER.

30:19.300 --> 30:20.494
- I'M GONNA GO
TO MY ROOM NOW.

30:20.640 --> 30:22.323
- WELL, HOW ABOUT
WE ALL JUST HANG OUT HERE,

30:22.470 --> 30:23.949
YOU CAN TELL US
ABOUT YOUR ADVENTURE?

30:24.090 --> 30:25.227
- ARE YOU OKAY?
- NO, I GOT TO FEED MY LIZARD.

30:25.370 --> 30:26.439
- OKAY.
- YOU DON'T WANT TO TELL US

30:26.580 --> 30:27.956
ABOUT THE RIDE
IN THE POLICE CAR?

30:28.100 --> 30:29.237
- NO, 'CAUSE I HAVE
TO FEED MY LIZARD.

30:29.370 --> 30:30.610
- ARE YOU HUNGRY, HONEY?
- ARE YOU SERIOUS?

30:30.750 --> 30:31.785
WE'RE NOT GONNA HAVE
A CONVERSATION ABOUT THIS?

30:31.930 --> 30:32.919
- HADDIE, PLEASE,
NOT RIGHT NOW.

30:33.070 --> 30:34.276
LET HIM FEED HIS LIZARD.

30:34.410 --> 30:35.752
- YOU TWO ARE NOT GONNA TALK
TO HIM?

30:35.900 --> 30:36.992
- HONEY, JUST LET HIM BE.
HE'S BEEN THROUGH A LOT TODAY.

30:37.140 --> 30:38.038
- NO, THAT'S NOT FAIR.

30:39.420 --> 30:40.580
- MAX.

30:43.150 --> 30:46.529
MAX, DO YOU UNDERSTAND
WHAT HAPPENED TODAY?

30:46.670 --> 30:48.945
- WELL, I WANTED
TO GO TO THE MUSEUM.

30:49.080 --> 30:52.629
- YES.
UM, WE KNOW.

30:52.780 --> 30:55.988
AND WHEN YOU JUST WANTED
TO LEAVE

30:56.130 --> 30:57.256
AND DIDN'T SAY ANYTHING,
DO YOU UNDERSTAND

30:57.400 --> 30:58.708
THAT WE HAD TO SPEND
OUR ENTIRE DAY

30:58.850 --> 31:02.160
WORRYING ABOUT YOU
AND WONDERING WHERE YOU ARE?

31:02.300 --> 31:03.858
- WELL, I DIDN'T GO
TO THE MUSEUM.

31:04.000 --> 31:04.739
I DIDN'T GET TO GO
TO THE MUSEUM.

31:04.890 --> 31:06.232
- OKAY. OKAY.

31:06.380 --> 31:08.473
WELL, DO YOU GET THAT?

31:08.620 --> 31:10.133
DO YOU CARE?

31:10.280 --> 31:11.486
- MAX, CAN YOU LOOK
AT YOUR SISTER?

31:11.620 --> 31:12.552
- DO YOU CARE?

31:12.690 --> 31:14.624
NO, YOU DON'T CARE,

31:14.760 --> 31:15.795
'CAUSE YOU NEVER CARE.

31:15.940 --> 31:16.895
OF COUR--
LIKE...

31:17.040 --> 31:17.938
- HADDIE.
- NO.

31:18.080 --> 31:19.559
WHAT, NO!
THIS ISN'T FAIR.

31:19.700 --> 31:22.874
MAX, YOU HAVE TO THINK
ABOUT OTHER PEOPLE.

31:23.010 --> 31:25.046
YOU ONLY THINK
ABOUT YOURSELF!

31:25.190 --> 31:26.976
I MEAN,
WHAT AM I SUPPOSED TO DO?

31:27.120 --> 31:29.259
EVERYTHING BECOMES SO HARD!

31:29.400 --> 31:33.746
WHY? LIKE, WHY DON'T YOU THINK
ABOUT ANYBODY BUT YOURSELF?

31:33.890 --> 31:34.504
- HADDIE.
- IT'S SO HARD!

31:34.650 --> 31:36.026
IT'S NOT FAIR.

31:36.170 --> 31:38.400
WE TRY SO HARD
TO MAKE THINGS NORMAL,

31:38.550 --> 31:42.304
AND IT'S JUST NOT.

31:42.450 --> 31:44.509
- IS SHE GONNA GET IN TROUBLE
FOR YELLING?

31:47.180 --> 31:48.624
I'M GONNA GO FEED GUACAMOLE.

31:48.760 --> 31:50.170
- OKAY.

31:54.800 --> 31:56.973
- [sighs]

31:59.530 --> 32:00.701
- HADDIE.

32:00.840 --> 32:03.468
- I KNOW.
I'M IN TROUBLE.

32:03.610 --> 32:05.464
- NO.
NO, YOU'RE NOT IN TROUBLE.

32:05.610 --> 32:07.293
- I'M REALLY SORRY.

